Q. What is an object?
   --> Everything around us is an object. For eg. keyboard,mouse, and so on.
       Objects can be defined based on how they look and how they behave.
       Objects in computer programming are also very similar. They have state(
       which helps us define how that object looks like) and behaviours( what that object
       does).



Q. What is Object oriented programming:
   --> is just a way of writing program.
Q. Why we should learn OOP?
   --> It simplify the development of large program.
   --> It will also help us maintain and modify the existing code.
   --> It helps use write more secure code.
   --> It helps us avoid duplicate code.
